XPS valence band spectra of the pure BiPO4 and 1wt% BN/BiPO4 sample were carried out to measure the total density of VB states and further determine the VB edges (Fig. 12
                        ) [45–47]. The valence band of pure BiPO4 was measured at about 2.58eV, while the band gap was calculated about 4.08eV (Fig. 6b). According to the formula ECB
                        =EVB-Eg, the conduction band of BiPO4 photocatalytic was presented at −1.50eV. The similar VB edge can be observed for 1wt % BN/BiPO4 sample, which indicated that the presence of graphene-like BN cannot influence the electronic structure of BiPO4.
